name: AZAD
bio: [('Beginning', "He grew up as a water polo player and started swimming competitively at age 16. He was 'discovered' while he was swimming laps at the town pool near his grandmother's home in 2010. (swimswam.com, 14 Apr 2016)"), ('Reason', '"Swimming is a way of life - it\'s not just a sport. It helps you throughout the long run. Getting up every morning, hopping into that cold pool, swimming and putting in heart and dedication." (kaleo.org, 11 Mar 2010)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralDUAL CITIZENHe and his family moved to the United States of America in 1996. He has dual citizenship in the Syrian Arab Republic and the United States of America. He was invited to apply for Syrian citizenship in order to represent the country internationally. (aljazeera.com, 20 Feb 2014; kaleo.org, 11 Mar 2010)OCCUPATIONIn 2007 he began working as a lifeguard at the Los Angeles County Fire Department Lifeguard Division in California, United States of America. He also makes hand paddles from recycled surfboards under the brand name EZ-A Handboards. He has an inventory in three local surf shops and sells his merchandise over social media. (washingtonpost.com, 13 Mar 2016) '), ('Relatives', "Muhsin al-Barazi, his grandfather's cousin, became prime minister of Syria in 1949 but was killed a month later by a firing squad during a coup d'etat. Juan Barazi, another relative, was a noted race car driver who competed in the Le Mans Series. (washingtonpost.com, 13 Mar 2016; aljazeera.com, 20 Feb 2014)"), ('Nickname', 'EZ-A (washingtonpost.com, 13 Mar 2016)'), ('Education', 'Human Movement Studies - University of Hawaii, Honolulu, HI, USA'), ('Languages', 'Arabic, English'), ('Hobbies', 'Surfing. name: TAREK
bio: [('Additional Information', 'GeneralFROM SYRIA TO GERMANYIn 2015 he moved from the Syrian Arab Republic to Germany to flee the war. He and Syrian cyclists Yalmaz Habash, Nazir Jaser and Nabil Allaham crossed the Mediterranean Sea together on a boat and then continued on foot. After 28 days they arrived in Germany by plane. (riffreporter.de, 04 Dec 2016; mopo.de, 20 Aug 2016) '), ('Injuries', 'In March 2017 he was involved in a crash during a race in Berlin, Germany. name: Mohamad
bio: [('Beginning', 'He began swimming at age five and took up triathlon in 2005. (olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017)'), ('Reason', '"I used to do long distance swimming and got a bit bored of swimming back and forth in the pool 60km per week. I tried a triathlon one weekend for fun, and I was hooked." (olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017)'), ('Coach', 'Kyla Rollinson [club] (triathlonmagazine.ca, 07 Feb 2017; olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017)'), ('Training', '"Depending on the day, I might do a 3-4km swimming workout, and then a bike or run interval session. At least once per week, I will do all three activities of the triathlon, but most days my training focuses on two." (olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (triathlonmagazine.ca, 07 Feb 2017)'), ('Memorable', 'Winning the 2008 Junior Elite Asian Cup Aquathlon in Thailand. (mo2.tokyo, 01 Jan 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralMOVE TO CANADAHe moved from Syria to Canada in 2010 in order to complete his studies and train at the highest level. "Training [in Syria] isn\'t always safe there. Sadly, less people are training. But there are people who are still trying." (triathlonmagazine.ca, 07 Feb 2017)OVERCOMING CHALLENGESSince moving to Canada in 2010 he has found it difficult not to worry about the situation in war-torn Syria. "My biggest challenge has been shifting my mindset and feelings from thinking about the war in Syria to thinking about and focusing on every single task during my day. This is still something I find challenging, but I have largely overcome this by talking and seeking support from friends, reading books, praying, and practising how to relax and breathe deeply." (olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017) '), ('Hero', 'US boxer Muhammad Ali. (olympichopeful.com, 15 Oct 2017)'), ('Nickname', 'Mo (mo2.tokyo, 01 Jan 2018)'), ('Education', 'Information Technology - Concordia University, Montreal, QC, CAN'), ('Languages', 'Arabic, English, French'), ('Hobbies', 'Reading, watching movies, going out with friends. (Facebook page, 02 Aug 2018)'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationResultAsian GamesDNQMen2010Guangzhou, CHNDNQWorld Triathlon SeriesDNFMen2017Edmonton, AB, CANDNFLAPMen2017Montreal, QC, CANLAPWorld Cup35Men2016Montreal, QC, CAN1:03:3650Men2016Salinas, ECU59:1157Men2018Huatulco, MEX1:00:48Asian Championships23Men2016Hatsukaichi, JPN2:01:2826Men2017Palembang, INA2:03:51')]

name: Majd Eddin
bio: [('Beginning', 'He took up athletics in 2005, beginning in long jump and triple jump before switching to high jump in 2006. (esyria.sy, 11 Aug 2011)'), ('Reason', 'His father encouraged him to get involved in the sport after seeing how tall he was becoming. (esyria.sy, 11 Aug 2011)'), ('Debut', '2007 for Syrian Arab Republic, in Jordan (iaaf.org, 25 Feb 2010)'), ('Coach', 'Imad Siraj [personal] (esyria.sy, 26 Aug 2017)'), ('Awards', 'He was flag bearer for the Syrian Arab Republic at the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games in 2012 and 2016. (iaaf.org, 09 Oct 2017; dailystar.com.lb, 19 May 2016)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralSPORTING DIFFICULTIESHe lives in Damascus, Syrian Arab Republic, and has experienced problems in obtaining visas since the conflict began there in 2011. He was unable to participate in the 2017 Diamond League meeting in Rabat, Morocco, after he was refused the necessary papers to enter the country, although he later managed to acquire a six-month visa that allowed him to compete in Europe through a Spanish embassy. He also has to go to Beirut, Lebanon, in order to travel to his events as there are no international flights to and from the Syrian Arab Republic. "I\'m an expert in embassies, where they are, their addresses, when they open, when they close, what documents you need for a visa. I\'m an administrative expert in this subject. Everyone is surprised when I say I still train and live in Syria, especially as I am among the top six in the world." (sport360.com, 09 Aug 2017)OCCUPATIONHe works for the Ministry of Education in the Syrian Arab Republic. (Facebook profile, 21 Apr 2018) '), ('Nickname', 'Jojo Jump (Facebook profile, 21 Apr 2018)'), ('Injuries', 'He was forced to battle a severe case of anaemia while competing at the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro.
